ular in the Middle Ages (when it was used for girls as well as boys), under the influence of a 3rd-century saint who was one of the seven deacons of Rome. He was martyred in  258 . The legend is that, having been required to hand over the Church's treasures to the civil authorities, he assembled the poor and sick and presented them. For this act of Christian defiance, he was roasted to death on a gridiron. In England the name is also associated with  St Laurence of Canterbury  (  d. 619 ). A more recent influence has been the actor  Sir Laurence Olivier  (  1907–89 ).  See also  Lawrence ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Laurence de Coggeshall was born about 1188, in Essex, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 2 sons. He died before 1261, in his hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1188–Bef 1261":"umbes 1188–enne 1261","1213–1305":"1213–1305","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1188–1261":"1188–1261","1305":"1305","Bef 1261":"enne 1261","1213":"1213","Abt 1188":"umbes 1188","1188":"1188","1220":"1220","1261":"1261","Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1188–Bef 1261":"noin 1188–ennen vuotta 1261","1213–1305":"1213–1305","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1188–1261":"1188–1261","1305":"1305","Bef 1261":"ennen vuotta 1261","1213":"1213","Abt 1188":"noin 1188","1188":"1188","1220":"1220","1261":"1261","Essex, England":"Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1188–Bef 1261":"environ 1188–avant 1261","1213–1305":"1213–1305","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1188–1261":"1188–1261","1305":"1305","Bef 1261":"avant 1261","1213":"1213","Abt 1188":"environ 1188","1188":"1188","1220":"1220","1261":"1261","Essex, England":"Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Laurence de Coggeshall est né environ 1188, à Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 2 fils. Il est décédé avant 1261, dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"Abt 1188–Bef 1261":"um 1188–vor 1261","1213–1305":"1213–1305","1220–Male":"1220–Verstorben","1188–1261":"1188–1261","1305":"1305","Bef 1261":"vor 